{
  "name": "migrate-all-remaining-shot-20260406-0324",
  "idea": "Migrate all remaining shot creation flows to use atomic RPCs and direct cache updates, eliminating the split-ownership pattern where mutations create partial cache entries and invalidation fills them in later. The create_shot_with_generations RPC and upsertShotInCache pattern from the previous megaplan (fix-the-fundamental-cache-20260406-0236) is the template. Flows to migrate: (1) createShotWithGenerationPath (singular) - uses create_shot_with_image RPC + applyAtomicShotCacheUpdate with partial optimistic data. Should use create_shot_with_generations RPC (N=1 case) instead. (2) createShotWithFilesPath - creates empty shot then uploads N files each triggering separate addImageToShot with own optimistic+invalidation. Needs post-upload upsertShotInCache with complete data. (3) useDuplicateAsNewGeneration - 4 sequential DB writes, no optimistic update, 5 separate invalidations. Needs atomic RPC. After migration, clean up: (4) Remove applyAtomicShotCacheUpdate (shotCacheUpdate.ts) - no longer needed once all paths use real data. (5) Remove setTimeout/delayed invalidation hacks. (6) Audit all enqueueGenerationsInvalidation callers - remove includeShots:true where cache is updated directly. (7) Remove the deprecated createShot field from CreateShotWithGenerationsPathInput. Be thorough - search for insertAutoPositionedShotGeneration, applyAtomicShotCacheUpdate, includeShots, setTimeout.*invalidat to find all instances.",
